  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The language being used is English.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this is tape number 7.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You asked me what my dreams or plans were in this rehabilitation camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, it wasn't a camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was more a castle, a large villa called [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was difficult to imagine [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] having a normal life without parents.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was a new phase of my life to reconcile myself to the fact that I'm alone.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it took many, many years to make peace with that realization.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Just as it was very hard [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to accept that the life that I was used to living will never return, that the pre-war era is gone forever.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think the first thoughts, although not jubilations of the end of the war and the liberation, was that now this is over, and life will return to normal.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so this next phase was to learn that it will never be so-called normal.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a-- a 15-year-old could not yet imagine a different life or a better life or a equal life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was seeking to-- to adjust, simply.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that did not happen overnight.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't believe so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think that this was-- there were no trained social workers or psychiatrists.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These were all volunteers or people who were trying to do the best for orphans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it's interesting because now, when I use the word 'orphan' and translate it into Czech, which is [CZECH] I don't think that I've ever used that in my life, that I'm an orphan.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that even shows you more that I was trying to ignore the fact and not make it acceptable as-- as even being labeled such.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
